commit.message: Update setup and requirements by removing unnecessary packages.

Refactor GCP backend to use traditional approach using client creds.

# The two previous methods (release as v0.5.0 and v0.4.0) all leverage
# the short-lived credentials, however, with those method either signing
# blobs are not offered, or credentials cannot be serialized. Due to
# the lack of a clear solution, this PR reverts the flow to the
# traditional and commonly used client credentials.
Add a GCP authz method that leverages domain-wide authority delegation.
Add missing error code and details to GCP general exception.
Add hints to GCP error messages.
Report error code and details for exceptions raised in the GCP backend.
Add methods to parse GCP errors.
Add description format to the build script.
